                            <comment id="77285" author="akilm" created="Thu, 29 Mar 2012 23:46:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a very similar issue. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The AuthenticationFailureBadCredentialsEvent gets fired as expected. &lt;br/&gt;
The AuthenticationSuccessEvent is also fired as expected &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but &lt;br/&gt;
AuthenticationFailureLockedEvent is not getting fired&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Akil&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="80837" author="rworsnop" created="Wed, 20 Jun 2012 10:42:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was introduced by the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-546&quot; title=&quot;Change ProviderManager to prevent hiding LockedExceptions when using multiple providers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-546&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-546&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. When a LockedException (or any other AccountStatusException) is thrown, ProviderManager will immediately rethrow the exception without trying other providers. It also skips the event publishing, which is what causes this bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I submitted a fix:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-security/pull/10&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-security/pull/10&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
